For each curve, after a rapid increase of stress to the highest (peak) value, it begins to gradually
decrease towards a steady state with varying degrees of softening, indicating the onset of dynamic
recrystallization (DRX). Furthermore, all ﬂowstress curves can be divided into three stages. In the ﬁrst
stage, in which there is a sharp increase in stress up to a critical value, the work hardening dominates.
In the second stage, the increase in stress is constantly slowed down to the peak value or the inﬂection
value of the work hardening rate, which corresponds to the increasing inﬂuence of dynamic recovery
and recrystallization. This e
